The paper deals with distributed algorithms in the LOCAL model, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses graph coloring, network-decompositions, and maximum degree, which are all topics in the sub-categories of Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Computational Complexity (cs.CC), Graph Theory (cs.GT), and Information Theory (cs.IT).
